Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated fasting glucose, creatinine, chloride, triglycerides, and LDL cholesterol, suggesting impaired renal function and increased cardiovascular risk. Other parameters, including liver function, electrolytes, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function, glycemic control, and lipid management in clinical context.
